cs.CL, cs.SI, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.CY 

This paper focuses on developing a neural network model for document classification on social media, which involves natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also incorporates user tastes, topic tastes, and user comments on posts, which involves social network analysis and information retrieval, making cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also mentions the use of deep learning models, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. Finally, the paper analyzes texts in forums and message boards, which involves cybersecurity and privacy concerns, making cs.CY (Computers and Society) a possible sub-category.
